The paper deals with auction mechanisms in search advertising, which involves game theory (cs.GT) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the concept of mutual benefit and cooperation, which are relevant to distributed systems (cs.DS) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper proposes an auction mechanism that maximizes welfare and revenue, which falls under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.EC).
